R was identified ca. 3 kb downstream of SCC {\textless}italic{\textgreater}mec{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} XI, indicating the presence of a possible SCC remnant. SCC {\textless}italic{\textgreater}mec{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} XI was also identified in the second CC130 MRSA isolate by PCR and sequencing. The CC130 MRSA isolates may be of animal origin as previously reported CC130 {\textless}italic{\textgreater}S. aureus{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} strains were predominantly from bovine sources. The highly divergent nature of SCC {\textless}italic{\textgreater}mec{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} XI relative to other SCC {\textless}italic{\textgreater}mec{\textless}/italic{\textgreater} elements indicates that it may have originated in another taxon. {\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
